events.name: PWA Workshop: PWA Starter Kit
events.description:
"PWA Workshop" je serija radionica pokrenutih u saradnji sa Naučno Tehnološkim Parkom Beograd, na kojima ćemo svakog prvog utorka u mesecu razmeniti iskustva o izradi PWA (Progressive Web Applications).

Na prvom sastanku ćemo pričati o PWA Starter Kit i tehnologijama koje koristi, kao što su lit-html, LitElement i Redux.

Vidimo se u NTParku u konferencijskoj sali zgrade B5.

events.name: Google Hash Code 2019
events.description:
Februar je mesec za Google Hash Code challenge pa će sad već tradicionalno GDG Beograd i ove godine biti domaćin svim zainteresovanim timovima za Online kvalifikacionu rundu timskog takmičenja u programiranju organizovanom od strane Google koja će se održati 28. Februara u 17:30. Timovi sa najboljim rezultatima prolaze u Finalnu rundu koja će se ove godine održati 27. Aprila u Google prostorijama u Dablinu.

Ovom prilikom pozivamo sve timove koji su se registrovali da se pridruže našem GDG Beograd Hub-u a one koji još uvek nemaju tim ili se nisu registrovali da to učine na http://g.co/hashcode i u toku registracije odaberu GDG Beograd Hub.

Napominjemo da morate registrovati tim na http://g.co/hashcode i u toku registracije odabrati GDG Beograd Hub kako biste mogli da učestvujete na takmičenju. Članovi koji nisu registrovani neće biti u mogućnosti da prisustvuju meetup-u!

Više informacija o samom takmičenju: hashcode.withgoogle.com

events.name: Online Speedrun Challenge: BigQuery, Kubernetes, ML and Cloud Run
events.description:
Hello!

We’re sure most of you have learning new technologies and tools as New Year’s resolutions. That’s why we’re excited to participate in the first Community Speedrun Challenge that Google is organizing for developer communities in Europe. And as part of the [Name of your community], you’re among the first to know about this!!

The Community Speedrun Challenge is a training program that will run in February where you’ll have the opportunity to join four Speedruns and get hands-on experience with tools like Kubernetes, Assistant, BigQuery our Cloud Run, Every Speedrun is open for a week to give you the ability to finish all labs in your best time, scoring more points and winning prizes.

Find more information and register here: bit.ly/speedrunchallenge0220

Schedule:

Speedrun Start Dates: February 3rd, 10th, 17th and 24th

Webinar Time: Mondays from 7pm to 9pm (GMT+1)

Topics:
* BigQuery Basics for Data Analysts
* Kubernetes in the Google Cloud
* Google Developer Essentials
* Hello Cloud Run.

events.name: [IWD] What it's like to be a woman in tech?
events.description:
International Women’s Day (IWD) is marked on March 8th every year. In different regions, the focus of celebrations ranges from general respect and appreciation toward women to a celebration of women’s economic, political, and social achievements.

Google Developer Group Beograd would like to celebrate International Women's Day, the 8th of March with special meetup event for all the ladies and gentlemen. We invite you all to join us and hear about Kesnija's journey in IT, and also give support and appreciation to all the ladies in tech.

Ksenija Vasiljevic, project manager at Endava, will give us great insights into the tech industry. She empowers women in tech and discovers if there are any prejudices around this topic. Her experience of 20 years in IT is inspiring and motivating for women to enter this hyper growing market. She is a living example that you can get that work-life balance on lockdown.

Let's hear her journey in tech.

Agenda:
18:00 - 18:10 - Welcome and introduction note
18:10 - 19:00 - Speaker talk
19:00 - 19:20 - Questions and answers
19:20 - 20:00 - Closing words and networking with food and drinks

Special thank you to Endava DOO for hosting the event and helping us celebrate International Women's Day.

*NOTE*
Tough the event is open to all we would appreciate registering on the form below so we know the number of attendees we can expect:

http://bit.ly/GDGmarch

events.name: Community Speedrun Challenge
events.description:
Hello!

We’re sure most of you are interested in learning new technologies and tools. That’s why we’re excited to participate in the Community Speedrun Challenge that Google is organizing for developer communities in Europe. And as part of the GDG Beograd, you’re among the first to know about this!!

Register here http://bit.ly/speedrunchallengeeurope

The Community Speedrun Challenge is a training program that will run in May where you’ll have the opportunity to join four Speedruns and get hands-on experience with Machine Learning on Google Cloud, and take your first steps with tools like BigQuery, Cloud Speech API, and Cloud ML Engine. Every Speedrun is open for a week to give you the ability to finish all labs in your best time, scoring more points and winning prizes.

Find more information and register here: http://bit.ly/speedrunchallengeeurope

Schedule:
Speedrun Start Dates: May 4, 11, 18, and 25
Webinar Time: Mondays from 7 pm to 9 pm (GMT+2)
Topics
Baseline: Data, ML, AI with Zack Akil (Google)
Intro to ML: Language Processing with Dale Markowitz (Google)
Intermediate ML with Lee Boonstra (Google)
BigQuery for Machine Learning with Felipe Hoffa (Google)
